<tr id="L156"><td><a href="#L156">156</a></td><td>LASARAN [on monitor]:  I can't wait for them to make arrangements. In fifteen minutes I am leaving here for the Dominion base on Soukara, and I have a feeling this is going to be the last time that they let me leave Cardassia Prime, so I need to take advantage of this opportunity.</td></tr>

<tr id="L157"><td><a href="#L157">157</a></td><td>WORF:  Soukara is inside Dominion controlled space. It will not be easy to make a rendezvous near that planet without being detected.</td></tr>

<tr id="L158"><td><a href="#L158">158</a></td><td>LASARAN [on monitor]:  Don't work your brain too hard, Klingon, I've taken care of everything. Three days from now, at exactly seventeen thirty hours local time, I will leave the base and walk into the jungle. It'll be at least two days before they know I'm missing. All you have to do is get me off the planet. Now, there are transporter scramblers protecting Soukara, so you can't beam me aboard your ship. You're going to have to land and meet me at a rendezvous point on foot. I'm sending you all the information you'll need to avoid the Dominion sensors on the ground. Follow my instructions, meet me at the rendezvous point and have a ship waiting.</td></tr>

<tr id="L159"><td><a href="#L159">159</a></td><td>DAX:  We've got the information. It looks pretty thorough.</td></tr>

